        <summary>Abstract</summary>
        <article class="has-text-justified p-2"> Creative accounting practices are characterized by excessive
          compilation and
          the use of novel ways of charactering income, expenditure, assets and liabilities.
          The study examined the influence of firm
          attributes on creative accounting in Nigerian quoted companies.
          Correlation and descriptive research designs were employed. Data
          were sourced from annual reports and accounts of 30 companies listed on the floor of
          Nigerian Stock Exchange for the period of 5-year (2011-2015). Multiple regression model
          was used and tested empirically, using the panel data and the relevant regression
          technique.
          The results indicate that profitability was positively and significantly associated
          with creative accounting proxy by discretionary accruals. It was also found that negative
          and insignificant relationship exists between financial leverage and creative accounting
          proxy by discretionary accruals in Nigerian quoted companies
          The study, recommended that
          regulators should enforce requirements for corporate reports among quoted companies on
          the floor of Nigerian Stock Exchange as to ensure a high quality of financial statements.</article>
